yle=\"background:#86d3e3;\"|\n| ''We Totally Rock!''\n| 1, 3\u20134\n| rowspan=4|4\n| May 14, 2019\n| 105 (\u201cWe Totally Rock!\u201d), 110 (\u201cSuper Shrimptennial Celebration!\u201d), 313 (\u201cParty at Sea!\u201d), & 404/405 (\u201cGuppy Style!)\n|}\n\n==Mobile streaming==\n* In May and September 2017, 20 episodes of the show were made available for streaming on the NOGGIN video service as one of three shows with interactive playalong episodes. Season 3 has the linear TV episodes while Season 4 has the interactive episodes.\n* Seasons 1-3 are currently available on [[Amazon Prime Video]] in the United States.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://bubbleguppies.nickjr.com/ Official Website]\n* {{IMDb title|0965404|Bubble Guppies}}\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for ''Bubble Guppies''\n|list =\n{{Annie Award for Best Animated Television Production}}\n{{Daytime Emmy Award for Outstanding Pre-School Children's Animated Program}}\n}}\n{{Nickelodeon original series}}\n[[Category:2010s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2020s American animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s Canadian animated television series]]\n[[Category:2020s Canadian animated television series]]\n[[Category:2011 American television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2011 Canadian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:American children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:American children's animated musical television series]]\n[[Category:American computer-animated television series]]\n[[Category:American television series revived after cancellation]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated fantasy television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated musical television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian computer-animated television series]]\n[[Category:Children's sketch comedy]]\n[[Category:English-language television programs]]\n[[Category:Mermaids in television]]\n[[Category:Fictional mermen and mermaids]]\n[[Category:Treehouse TV shows]]\n[[Category:Nick Jr. original programming]]\n[[Category:American preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian preschool education television series]]\n[[Category:Television series by DHX Media]]\n[[Category:Television series by Nelvana]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about children]]\n[[Category:Animated television series about fish]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|US children's television series}}\n{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Bubble Guppies\n| image                    = BubbleGuppieslogo.png <!--Please do not place copyrighted images-->\n| genre                    = [[Animation]]<ref name=CommonSenseMedia>{{cite web|url=https://www.commonsensemedia.org/tv-reviews/bubble-guppies|title=Bubble Guppies|work=commonsensemedia.org|accessdate=30 April 2015}}</ref><br>[[Pre-school]]<br>[[Musical film|Musical]]<br>[[Comedy]]<br>[[Sketch comedy]] (Seasons 1-4)<br>[[Fantasy]] (Season 5-present)\n| creator                  = Jonny Belt<br />Robert Scull\n| developer                = \n| writer                   = \n| creative_director        = \n| presenter                = Zachary Gordon (2011)<br>Jacob Bertrand (2011-2013)<br>Taylor Kaplan (2019-2020 present)<br>Quinn Breslin (2019-2020 present)<br>Frank Welker<br>Tino Insana (2011-2020)<br>Fred Tatasciore (2012-2015)\n| voices                   = Brianna Gentilella<br>Taylor Kaplan<br>[[Zachary Gordon]]<br>Jacob Bertrand<br>Quinn Breslin<br>Jelani Imani<br>Caleb Clarke<br>Angelina Wahler<br>Selena Ann Gonzalez<br>[[Grace Kaufman]]<br>Reyna Shaskan<br>Eamon Pirruccello<br>Jet Jurgensmyer<br>AJ Kane<br>Hayden Hunter<br>Abriella Bierer<br>Lauren Reichwald<br>Lewis Dillon<br>Harriet Perring<br>Will Matthews<br>Andy Turvey<br>Emma Tate<br>John Campbell<br>Amba Bierer<br>Edward Cross<br>Megan North<br>Sam Brown<br>[[Fra